://github.com/efeslab/ada-portathon
ADA Portathon 3/7/2018

|- General Changes in All Benchmarks:

Set CC=${TARGET_CC}
Change gcc to $(CC) in Makefiles if applicable
Set the TARGET_CC environmental variable as $riscvgcc when cross-compiling with:

export TARGET_CC=$riscvgcc

|- MiBench/network/patricia

Error: patricia_test.c:46:10: fatal error: rpc/rpc.h: No such file or directory
Fix: Include the sunrpc directory from riscv-glibc

RISCV_FLAGS=-I/home/ada/portathon/freedom-u-sdk/riscv-gnu-toolchain/riscv-glibc/sunrpc/

$(CC) -static patricia.c patricia_test.c $(RISCV_FLAGS) -O3 -o patricia

Run Scripts Changes:
$runqemu ./dijkstra_large(or small) input.dat > output_large(or small).dat

|- MiBench/office/rsynth

Requires <multimedia/libaudio.h> which is not available in RISCV toolchain.

|- MiBench/security/pgp

Assembly sources need manual translation to RISCV.

|- MiBench/security/rijndael

Invalid casting of fpos_t struct to char in source code, change to:

inbuf[0] = ((char) flen.__pos & 15) | (inbuf[0] & ~15);

|- MiBench/security/sha

Use of GCC strip binary depends on target architecture:

ifeq ($(CC), $(riscvgcc))
        /home/ada/portathon/freedom-u-sdk/toolchain/bin/riscv64-unknown-linux-gnu-strip $@
else
        strip $@
endif


